field.value:
If a default layout includes a view component, the capturefor() blocks are not rendered. The rest of content is, just not the capturefor. eg Views\layouts\default.vm <html >... <script type="text/javascript"> $!scripts </script> ..<div> #component(DivisionSelectComponent) </div... ...</html>
Views\components\DivisionalSelectComponent\default.vm #capturefor(scripts) var division;
function onDivisionChange(e,a){ alert('changed'); alert(this.value);
} #end
<select id="divisionSelect" name="divisionSelect"> <option>Force Total</option> <option value="AA">North West Leeds</option> <option value="BA">North East Leeds</option> </select>
When the view is rendered, the divisionSelect list is rendered, but the code onDivisionChange is not. If the view passes the component into a named section, it all renders fine.
